CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 18, 1959, pg. B4 reads: "Uninvited Throws Brick - When Barbara Williams held a party in honor of her 16th birthday Friday, at 7211 Mount Vernon St., where her parents and her grandmother, Mrs. Ora Simms, Republican political figure, live, several young boys who had not been invited, tried to "crash" the party but were turned away. Finally, one of the boys threw a brick through the window and all of the boys ran.  Police, notified, and given names, have failed to make an arrest. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Broken window at home of Mr. and Mrs. Williams and Ora Sims during birthday party for Barbara Williams, 7211 Mount Vernon Street
